    "narrative_summary": "The BRCA1 c.1231G>A (p.D411N) missense change is a rare germline variant that has been examined in the context of hereditary breast and ovarian cancer risk. It is listed in several BRCA variant compilations but has not been definitively linked to disease.\n\nClinical databases and multifactorial likelihood analyses consistently classify D411N as a variant of uncertain significance. The variant appears in supplementary tables of two recent evolutionary studies that label it \u201cuncertain significance\u201d [PMC8860097, PMC10993466] and a large ENIGMA\u2010based quantitative analysis that reports a non\u2011informative combined likelihood ratio and retains the VUS status [PMC6772163]. A machine\u2011learning model trained on known pathogenic and benign BRCA1 variants predicts D411N to be pathogenic, providing a computational argument for deleteriousness [PMC8062186]; however, no independent clinical segregation or case\u2011control data supporting this prediction are presented.\n\nFunctional investigations of D411N are limited to computational assessments of potential disruption of phosphorylation motifs. In a survey of BRCA1 missense variants affecting kinase sites, D411N is listed only as \u201cbiologically uncharacterized\u201d without experimental evidence of altered protein function or impact on DNA repair pathways [PMC3660339]. No other in\u2011vitro or in\u2011vivo functional assays have been reported for this change.\n\nPopulation data show a single observation of D411N in the non\u2011Finnish European subset of gnomAD, insufficient to inform frequency\u2011based classification and yielding a non\u2011informative likelihood ratio in the multifactorial framework [PMC6772163]. Computational annotations beyond the phosphorylation\u2011motif analysis consist of the aforementioned pathogenicity prediction from a random\u2011forest model, but no additional in silico scores or consensus deleteriousness metrics are provided.\n\nOverall, the preponderance of evidence retains BRCA1 D411N in the category of uncertain significance. While a predictive algorithm suggests possible pathogenicity, the lack of functional validation, limited population data, and the absence of supportive clinical segregation or case\u2011control evidence mean that current data are insufficient to reclassify the variant as pathogenic or benign.",
    "structured_summary": {
